# K-Means Clustering Analysis on Bank Data

## Project Description

This project applies K-Means clustering on bank data to group similar banks based on their financial and operational characteristics.
The main goal is to identify hidden patterns in the dataset using unsupervised machine learning.

## Objective

To segment banks into meaningful clusters and analyze the similarities and differences between each cluster.

## Tools Used

* Python
* Jupyter Notebook
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Scikit-learn

## Steps Performed

* Loaded and inspected the dataset
* Checked missing values and duplicate records
* Treated outliers using IQR capping
* Removed the Bank ID column from clustering
* Standardized numerical features
* Used Elbow Method and Silhouette Score to select clusters
* Applied K-Means clustering
* Added cluster labels to the dataset
* Analyzed and interpreted cluster profiles

## Conclusion

The K-Means model successfully grouped banks into different clusters based on similar data patterns.
These clusters can help in understanding bank profiles, identifying performance differences, and supporting better decision-making through data-driven segmentation.
